Reviewing the current [CQL|https://developer.atlassian.com/confdev/confluence-rest-api/advanced-searching-using-cql] docs, I don't see a possibility to limit the return results, only query by specific age?

What I want is a rolling window of the most recent 50 blog posts in a space, as a remote addon, I'd have to get the last month, then the next, to build up the quota.  Supporting a limit parameter, not unlink SQL, "limit=50" would allow content volume restriction, which is not currently possible.

